00310  */
00311 returnValue MessageHandling::throwError(
00312         returnValue Enumber,
00313         const char* additionaltext,
00314         const char* functionname,
00315         const char* filename,
00316         const unsigned long linenumber,
00317         VisibilityStatus localVisibilityStatus
00318         )
00319 {
00320         /* consistency check */
00321         if ( Enumber <= SUCCESSFUL_RETURN )
00322                 return throwError( RET_ERROR_UNDEFINED,0,__FUNCTION__,__FILE__,__LINE__,VS_VISIBLE );
00323 
00324         /* Call to common throwMessage function if error shall be displayed. */
00325         if ( errorVisibility == VS_VISIBLE )
00326                 return throwMessage( Enumber,additionaltext,functionname,filename,linenumber,localVisibilityStatus,"ERROR" );
00327         else
00328                 return Enumber;
00329 }

00399 returnValue MessageHandling::listAllMessages( )
00400 {
00401         #ifndef __XPCTARGET__
00402         int keypos = 0;
00403         char myPrintfString[160];
00404 
00405         /* Run through whole returnValueList and print each item. */
00406         while ( returnValueList[keypos].key != TERMINAL_LIST_ELEMENT )
00407         {
00408                 snprintf( myPrintfString,160," %d - %s \n",keypos,returnValueList[keypos].data );
00409                 myPrintf( myPrintfString );
00410 
00411                 ++keypos;
00412         }
00413         #endif
00414 
00415         return SUCCESSFUL_RETURN;
00416 }

00425 /*
00426  *      t h r o w M e s s a g e
00427  */
00428 returnValue MessageHandling::throwMessage(
00429         returnValue RETnumber,
00430         const char* additionaltext,
00431         const char* functionname,
00432         const char* filename,
00433         const unsigned long linenumber,
00434         VisibilityStatus localVisibilityStatus,
00435         const char* RETstring
00436         )
00437 {
00438         #ifndef __SUPPRESSANYOUTPUT__
00439         #ifndef __XPCTARGET__
00440         int keypos = 0;
00441         char myPrintfString[160];
00442 
00443         /* 1) Determine number of whitespace for output. */
00444         char whitespaces[41];
00445         int numberOfWhitespaces = (errorCount-1)*2;
00446 
00447         if ( numberOfWhitespaces < 0 )
00448                 numberOfWhitespaces = 0;
00449 
00450         if ( numberOfWhitespaces > 40 )
00451                 numberOfWhitespaces = 40;
00452 
00453         memset( whitespaces, ' ', (size_t) numberOfWhitespaces );
00454         whitespaces[numberOfWhitespaces] = '\0';
00455 
00456         /* 2) Find error/warning/info in list. */
00457         while ( returnValueList[keypos].key != TERMINAL_LIST_ELEMENT )
00458         {
00459                 if ( returnValueList[keypos].key == RETnumber )
00460                         break;
00461                 else
00462                         ++keypos;
00463         }
00464 
00465         if ( returnValueList[keypos].key == TERMINAL_LIST_ELEMENT )
00466         {
00467                 throwError( RET_EWI_UNDEFINED,0,__FUNCTION__,__FILE__,__LINE__,VS_VISIBLE );
00468                 return RETnumber;
00469         }
00470 
00471         /* 3) Print error/warning/info. */
00472         if ( ( returnValueList[keypos].globalVisibilityStatus == VS_VISIBLE ) && ( localVisibilityStatus == VS_VISIBLE ) )
00473         {
00474 
00475                 if ( errorCount > 0 )
00476                 {
00477                         snprintf( myPrintfString,160,"%s->", whitespaces );
00478                         myPrintf( myPrintfString );
00479                 }
00480 
00481                 if ( additionaltext == 0 )
00482                 {
00483                         #ifdef __DEBUG__
00484                         snprintf(       myPrintfString,160,"%s (%s, %s:%d): \t%s\n",
00485                                                 RETstring,functionname,filename,(int)linenumber,returnValueList[keypos].data
00486                                                 );
00487                         #else
00488                         snprintf(       myPrintfString,160,"%s:  %s\n",
00489                                                                         RETstring,returnValueList[keypos].data
00490                                                 );
00491                         #endif
00492                         myPrintf( myPrintfString );
00493                 }
00494                 else
00495                 {
00496                         #ifdef __DEBUG__
00497                         snprintf(       myPrintfString,160,"%s (%s, %s:%d): \t%s %s\n",
00498                                                 RETstring,functionname,filename,(int)linenumber,returnValueList[keypos].data,additionaltext
00499                                                 );
00500                         #else
00501                         snprintf(       myPrintfString,160,"%s:  %s %s\n",
00502                                                 RETstring,returnValueList[keypos].data,additionaltext
00503                                                 );
00504                         #endif
00505                         myPrintf( myPrintfString );
00506                 }
00507 
00508                 /* take care of proper indention for subsequent error messages */
00509                 if ( RETstring[0] == 'E' )
00510                 {
00511                         ++errorCount;
00512                 }
00513                 else
00514                 {
00515                         if ( errorCount > 0 )

00531                                                                                                         )

00535         /* 2) Find error/warning/info in list. */

00537         {
